08},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Broad Chalke is in the Salisbury area of Wiltshire (SP5), and sits in the rural-to-commuter belt around Salisbury. Historic references and parish records show long-established settlement patterns, with modern housing mostly as infill around older cores. Day-to-day life depends on local village facilities plus Salisbury for larger services. The area appeals to buyers who want a quieter setting but still need practical links to the city.","character":"Broad Chalke has a village-scale layout with mixed period and modern homes, a parish-centred feel, and surrounding countryside as a dominant part of daily character.","amenities":["Parish/community facilities in Broad Chalke","Nearby shopping and services in Salisbury","Local walking routes and countryside access"],"schools":[{"name":"Primary schools serving Broad Chalke","phase":"Primary","distance":"typically local catchment / short drive","url":"https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/"},{"name":"Secondary schools in Salisbury","phase":"Secondary","distance":"usually reached by bus or car","url":"https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/"}],"transport":{"nearestStation":"Salisbury","roads":"Village roads generally connect to the A36/A30 corridor for Salisbury access.","commutes":[{"to":"Salisbury","time":"often around 10-30 minutes by car depending on exact start point and traffic","mode":"Car","source":"https://www.google.com/maps"},{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"typically around 1h30-1h40 from Salisbury station services","mode":"Rail (from Salisbury)","source":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/stations/salisbury/"}]},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SP5.html","asOf":"2026-05-24"},"thingsToDo":["Village and valley walks","Visits to Salisbury Cathedral/cultural venues","Trips to local heritage sites and surrounding countrys